raining as a (a) nurse, (b) midwife and (c) GP in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","170904"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968354","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-09-10","<p>Data on the number of addiction services and centres, and detox beds which have closed since 2010 are not collected centrally.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-09-10T17:09:26.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968354/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968354/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968354/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-09-05","Addictions: Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether his Department collects data on the number of (a) addiction services and centres and (b) detox beds which have closed since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","170905"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968356","Cabinet Office","false","2018-09-13","<p>We do not hold a central record of all those who hold roles in the department, either paid or unpaid, who are members of the House of Lords.</p><p> </p><p>The Cabinet Office has responsibility for nine NDPBs covering a range of advisory functions which include, for example, the House of Lords Appointments Commission and the Committee on Standards in Public Life. Membership of the Boards is publically available on Gov.uk. There are currently 10 Peers on the Boards of Cabinet Office NDPBs.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-09-13T11:07:47.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968356/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968356/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968356/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-09-05","Cabinet Office: Peers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many members of the House of Lords hold (a) paid and (b) unpaid roles within (i) his Department and (ii) his Department's agencies.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","170906"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968357","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-09-10","<p>NHS Improvement collects data on backlog maintenance annually from National Health Service trusts through its Estates Returns Information Collection. The data collected has not been amended centrally and its accuracy always remains the responsibility of the contributing NHS organisations. It can be found at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/559126/est-ret-info-col-2015-2016-Report.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/559126/est-ret-info-col-2015-2016-Report.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>The estimated cost required to eliminate backlog maintenance work in the NHS in the current financial year will be published in October 2018. The estimated cost required to eliminate backlog maintenance work in the NHS in the last three years is:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Total cost to eradicate backlog</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>£ million</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>4,042</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>4,338</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>4,975</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>5,546</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Backlog maintenance amounts and risks will change over time due to a number of reasons including the prioritisation of investment to reduce it, disposal of buildings with backlog maintenance, changes to estate and clinical standards, the aging of the estate and changes in the costs of capital work.</p><p> </p><p>The Autumn Budget announced £3.5 billion of new additional capital investment in the NHS in England by 2022-23, including £700 million to support turnaround plans in struggling trusts and tackle critical maintenance issues.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-09-10T16:10:45.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968357/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968357/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968357/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-09-05","NHS: Repairs and Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what estimate he has made of the funding required from the public purse to remove the backlog of maintenance work in the NHS in (a) 2015-16, (b) 2016-17, (c) 2017-18 and (d) the 2018-19 financial year.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","170907"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968358","Treasury","false","2018-09-14","<p>The Treasury Ministers, Special Advisers and additional Ministers are published in the Annual report and Accounts. Please see the Remuneration and Staff Report chapter (pages 66-69) at the following link</p><p> </p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hm-treasury-annual-report-and-accounts-2017-to-2018</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-09-14T13:12:08.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968358/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968358/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968358/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-09-05","Treasury: Peers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many members of the House of Lords hold (a) paid and (b) unpaid roles within (i) his Department and (ii) his Department's agencies.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","170908"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968359","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-09-14","<p>The Department estimates the amount of unpaid overtime worked by National Health Service staff from self reported information in the NHS Staff Survey. The following table shows this data for each of the last five years.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Percentage of staff working additional unpaid hours (%)</p></td><td><p>Up to 5 hours (%)</p></td><td><p>6-10 hours (%)</p></td><td><p>11 or more hours (%)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>57.60</p></td><td><p>44</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>59.22</p></td><td><p>44</p></td><td><p>12</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>60.48</p></td><td><p>45</p></td><td><p>12</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>59.07</p></td><td><p>45</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017</p></td><td><p>58.34</p></td><td><p>44</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>We recognise and value the commitment of NHS staff in serving patients and the public. For staff employed under Agenda for Change (AfC) Section 3 of the NHS Terms and Conditions of Service Handbook gives a right to overtime payment or time off in lieu (TOIL).</p><p> </p><p>The recently agreed NHS Employers framework agreement states “Employing organisations will work in partnership with trade unions to introduce local mechanisms to guarantee access to those annual leave and TOIL provisions set out in the NHS Terms and Conditions of Service handbook.” (paragraph 6.1). It is available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.nhsemployers.org/your-workforce/2018-contract-refresh/framework-agreement" target="_blank">http://www.nhsemployers.org/your-workforce/2018-contract-refresh/framework-agreement</a></p><p> </p><p>This work will be taken forward by the NHS Staff Council this year. It is envisaged the Council will examine if there are issues with staff being unable to take their annual leave or TOIL and look at guidance. The Handbook already contains a provision which states that if TOIL cannot be taken within three months it should be paid at overtime rates (Section 3 paragraph 5).</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-09-14T11:05:38.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968359/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968359/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968359/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-09-05","NHS: Overtime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what estimate he has made of the amount of unpaid overtime worked by NHS staff in each of the last five years for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","170909"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968360","Cabinet Office","false","2018-09-10","<p>Building on a previous Cabinet Office funding review undertaken in 2013/14, which led to a number of significant changes including a new model that provides more accurate allocations for Returning Officers (ROs) and the subsequent establishment of an in-house Elections Claims Unit to assess claims, we are currently undertaking further work to review the funding arrangements for national polls.</p><p> </p><p>This work has two main objectives: to promote best value for use of taxpayers’ money; and to improve the effectiveness and efficiency of the processes that manage expenditure and provide more transparent reporting on the costs of nationwide polls.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2018-09-10T15:40:54.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968360/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968360/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968360/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-09-05","Returning Officers: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps the Government is taking to improve the administration of (a) fees and (b) charges of Returning Officers for parliamentary elections.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","170910"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968361","Home Office","false","2018-09-13","<p>Baroness Williams of Trafford holds a paid role within the Home Office as Minister of State for Countering Extremism and Parliamentary Under Secretary of State (Minister for Equalities)</p><p>Baroness Nuala O’Loan of Kirkinriola chairs the Daniel Morgan Independent Panel. This role is paid for by the Home Office, though the Panel operates independently of government.</p><p>There are no further members of the House of Lords holding either a paid or unpaid role in the Home Office or its agencies.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-09-13T16:49:58.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968361/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968361/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968361/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-09-05","Home Office: Peers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many members of the House of Lords hold (a) paid and (b) unpaid roles within (i) his Department and (ii) his Department's agencies.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","170911"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968363","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-09-12","<p>Special Measures for Quality was introduced in July 2013 and Special Measures for Finance was introduced in July 2016. The information is shown in the following tables.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Numbers of trusts in Special Measures for Quality, per year</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>National Health Service trust</p></td><td><p>Foundation trust</p></td><td><p>Total</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Current (as of September 2018)</p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>13</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2018 (from January to August)</p></td><td><p>11</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>17</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017</p></td><td><p>13</p></td><td><p>9</p></td><td><p>22</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>12</p></td><td><p>8</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>11</p></td><td><p>18</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>8</p></td><td><p>14</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Numbers of trusts in Special Measures for Finance, per year</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>NHS trust</p></td><td><p>Foundation trust</p></td><td><p>Total</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Current (as of September 2018)</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>11</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2018 (from January to August)</p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>12</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017</p></td><td><p>8</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>14</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-09-12T15:35:57.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968363/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968363/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968363/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-09-05","NHS: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many (a) NHS trusts and (b) Foundation Trusts have been placed in (i) special measures and (ii) financial special measures in each year since 2012; how many of those Trusts remain in special measures.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","170912"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968364","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-09-13","<p>We do not hold a central record of all those who hold roles, either paid or unpaid, who are members of the House of Lords.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-09-13T16:11:51.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968364/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968364/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968364/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-09-05","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Peers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many members of the House of Lords hold (a) paid and (b) unpaid roles within (i) his Department and (ii) his Department's agencies.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","170913"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968365","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-09-14","<p>The requested information is presented in the following table. Retainers, registrar and locum numbers are not comparable across the timescale requested and have therefore been excluded.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>All practitioners (excluding retainers and registrars and locums) headcount per 100,000 population</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>66.5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>66.5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>65.5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>63.6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017</p></td><td><p>62.0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: NHS Digital</p><p> </p><p>Notes:</p><p> </p><ol><li>All data as at 30 September for the relevant year.</li><li>Prior to 2015 figures are sourced from National Health Application and Infrastructure Services general practitioner (GP) Payments (Exeter) System. From 2015 figures are sourced from the workforce Minimum Dataset and include estimates for missing data.</li><li>GP Headcount per 100,000 population figures calculated based on the Office for National Statistics figures for England population that were available at the time the relevant GP headcount figures were originally published.</li></ol>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-09-14T13:40:02.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968365/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968365/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968365/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-09-05","General Practitioners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many practising GPs there were in England per 100,000 population in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","170914"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968366","Home Office","false","2018-09-10","<p>The Disclosure and Barring Service publish police performance and average turnaround times quarterly with the latest information available up to and including June 2018.</p><p>Average turnaround times for police disclosure units broken down by month and by force can be found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/dbs-performance" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/dbs-performance</a></p><p>Police Force Disclosure Units must provide locally held information for inclusion on enhanced criminal record certificates in accordance with a statutory test set out in Part V of the Police Act 1997. This test requires that a chiefofficer believes the information to be relevant and that it ought to be disclosed. When considering information for disclosure, chief officers must also haveregard to statutory guidance available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/statutory-disclosure-guidance" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/statutory-disclosure-guidance</a></p><p> </p><p>The statutory guidance sits alongside operational guidance drawn up by the police service and the Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS).</p><p>This Quality Assurance Framework (QAF) can be found at the link below:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/quality-assurance-framework-version-nine-qaf-v9" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/quality-assurance-framework-version-nine-qaf-v9</a></p><p>The application of the Quality Assurance Framework by Police Force Disclosure Units is monitored by the DBS Standard and Compliance Unit to help ensure that a consistent high quality approach is taken by forces when they process DBS applications.</p><p>DBS performance is measured against Published Service Standards which are detailed in the DBS Business Plan. These include:</p><ul><li>To complete 87% of all standard and enhanced DBS checks within 21 days</li><li>To complete 96% of all standard and enhanced DBS checks within 42 days</li><li>To complete 90% of DBS basic checks within 14 days</li></ul><p>The DBS performance against these targets is published quarterly, here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/dbs-dataset-1-disclosure-progress-information-disclosed-and-update-service-subscriptions" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/dbs-dataset-1-disclosure-progress-information-disclosed-and-update-service-subscriptions</a></p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-09-10T16:23:15.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968366/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968366/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968366/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-09-05","Vetting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the average time taken was from request to response to carry out vetting under the disclosure and barring regulations in each police force in England and Wales in the last period for which figures are available; whether that vetting is undertaken in accordance with national requirements in each such force; and (a) what his policy is on and (b) how he measures the performance of the Disclosure and Barring Service.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","170694"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968367","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-09-13","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union can confirm that 1 member of the House of Lords has a paid role in the Department. Lord Callanan was appointed Minister of State at the Department for Exiting the European Union on 27 October 2017.</p><p> </p>","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris",,"2018-09-13T15:13:28.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968367/answer","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968367/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968367/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-09-05","Department for Exiting the European Union: Peers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many members of the House of Lords hold (a) paid and (b) unpaid roles within (i) his Department and (ii) his Department's agencies.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","170915"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968368","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-09-13","<p>The average waiting time for a general practitioner (GP) appointment is not collected or held centrally. In the 2018 GP patient survey 61.6% of respondents (who could remember whether or not they were able to get an appointment, and when they wanted the appointment) stated they saw or spoke to someone at a time they wanted to or sooner. NHS England is working with NHS Digital to consider ways of improving the availability and quality of GP data, including waiting times data.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has committed to improving access to general practice services by 2019. This includes ensuring there are sufficient routine appointments available at evenings and weekends to meet locally determined demand, alongside effective access to out of hours and urgent care services. The latest National Health Service planning guidance, issued by NHS England in February 2018, requires clinical commissioning groups to provide extended access to general practice to their whole population by 1 October 2018, to ensure additional capacity is in place ahead of winter 2018.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-09-13T13:15:08.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968368/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968368/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968368/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-09-05","General Practitioners: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what the average waiting time to see a GP in England was in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","170916"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968369","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-09-13","<p>The Ministry of Defence does not hold a central record of roles held, either paid or unpaid, by Members of the House of Lords.</p><p>However, I can confirm that The Rt Hon Earl Howe is the current Minister of State for Defence and serves in an unpaid capacity.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-09-13T14:31:09.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968369/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968369/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968369/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-09-05","Ministry of Defence: Peers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many members of the House of Lords hold (a) paid and (b) unpaid roles within (i) his Department and (ii) his Department's agencies.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","170917"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968370","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-09-14","<p>It is for National Health Service trusts and foundation trusts to agree their 2018-19 plans locally with commissioners. NHS England and NHS Improvement have been leading the annual planning process for 2018-19, and have worked with providers and commissioners to produce a balanced plan for 2018-19. NHS Improvement published their Quarter 1 assessment of the NHS providers' plans in the ‘quarterly performance of the NHS provider sector’ on 11 September 2018. This is available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://improvement.nhs.uk/resources/quarterly-performance-nhs-provider-sector-quarter-1-201819/" target="_blank">https://improvement.nhs.uk/resources/quarterly-performance-nhs-provider-sector-quarter-1-201819/</a></p><p> </p><p>The long-term plan being developed by NHS leaders, clinicians, and health experts is expected to work towards ensuring no NHS organisation is in financial deficit.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-09-14T10:56:19.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968370/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968370/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968370/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-09-05","NHS: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what estimate he has made of the number of (a) NHS trusts and (b) NHS foundation trusts that will be in deficit at the end of the 2018-19 financial year; and whether he projects the NHS trust sector as a whole to be in deficit at the end of that year.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","170918"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968371","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-09-14","<p>We do not hold a central record of all those who hold roles, either paid or unpaid, who are members of the House of Lords</p>","Charnwood","Edward Argar",,"2018-09-14T12:25:47.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968371/answer","Biography information for Edward Argar","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968371/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968371/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-09-05","Ministry of Justice: Peers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many members of the House of Lords hold (a) paid and (b) unpaid roles within (i) his Department and (ii) his Department's agencies.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","170919"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968373","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-09-13","<p>The following members of the House of Lords currently hold paid public appointments with the Department’s arm’s length bodies:</p><p> </p><p>- Lord Adebowale, as Non-Executive Director of NHS England;</p><p>- Lord Carter, as Non-Executive Director of NHS Improvement;</p><p>- Lord Darzi, as Non-Executive Director of NHS Improvement;</p><p>- Baroness Harding, as Chair of NHS Improvement;</p><p>- Lord Oates, as Non-Executive Director of NHS Blood and Transplant; and</p><p>- Lord Ribeiro, as Chair of the Independent Reconfiguration Panel.</p><p> </p><p>Public appointments are managed in accordance with the Governance Code on Public Appointments.</p><p> </p><p>The following members of the House of Lords also hold paid roles:</p><p> </p><p>- Lord Bishop of Norwich, as Chair of the Paterson Inquiry;</p><p>- Lord Carter, as Chair of the NHS Procurement and Efficiency Board;</p><p>- Baroness Cumberlege, as Chair of the Independent Medicines and Medical Devices Safety Review;</p><p>- Baroness Finlay, as Chair of the National Mental Capacity Act Forum (joint role between the Department of Health and Social Care and Ministry of Justice);</p><p>- Baroness Neuberger, as Vice Chair of the Independent Review of the Mental Health Act; and</p><p>- Lord Patel, as Chair of Social Work England (joint role between the Department of Health and Social Care and the Department for Education).</p><p> </p><p>Lord Darzi holds an unpaid role as Chair of the Accelerated Access Collaborative and Baroness Lane-Fox holds an unpaid role as one of the independent experts invited by the Government to provide advice and support engagement in advance of the green paper on social care.</p><p> </p><p>No members of the House of Lords currently hold roles with the Department’s Executive Agencies, Public Health England and the Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency.</p><p> </p><p>Lord O’Shaughnessy is Parliamentary Under Secretary of State for Health.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-09-13T11:03:01.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968373/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968373/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968373/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-09-05","Department of Health and Social Care: Peers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many members of the House of Lords hold (a) paid and (b) unpaid roles within (i) his Department and (ii) his Department's agencies.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","170920"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968374","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-09-13","<p>Our assessment of the merits of ending the sale of energy drinks to children is available in the impact assessment published on 30 August as part of the consultation on this proposed measure.</p><p> </p><p>The consultation and impact assessment are available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/ending-the-sale-of-energy-drinks-to-children" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/consultations/ending-the-sale-of-energy-drinks-to-children</a></p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-09-13T13:24:07.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968374/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968374/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968374/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-09-05","Energy Drinks: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment he has made of the merits of banning the sale of energy drinks to children.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","170921"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968375","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-09-11","<p>In 2020/21 the Government aims to increase local government’s retention of business rates from 50 per cent to 75 per cent.</p><p>Increasing the level of business rates retention to 100 per cent remains the Government’s long-term ambition.</p><p>That is why, this year we are operating 100 per cent business rates retention pilots in 16 areas across the country. Next year we will also pilot 75 per cent business rates retention to aid understanding of how we transition into the proposed new system in 2020/21. Moving to greater rates retention will give local authorities more control of the money they raise locally.</p><p>The current 50 per cent business rates retention scheme is yielding strong results with local authorities estimating that in 2018/19 they will keep around £2.4 billion in business rates growth.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2018-09-11T15:02:09.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968375/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968375/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968375/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-09-05","Non-domestic Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, whether it is the Government's policy to enable local authorities to retain business rates collected.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","170922"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968376","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-09-14","<p>The Department has one paid role for a member of the House of Lords, Lord Henley, who represents the government in the House of Lords. The Department has no unpaid roles for members of the House of Lords.</p><p> </p><p>The Department has 40 Partner Organisations where members of the House of Lords have roles. One role is unpaid; the other eight roles are paid.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-09-14T13:53:44.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968376/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968376/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968376/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-09-05","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Peers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many members of the House of Lords hold (a) paid and (b) unpaid roles within (i) his Department and (ii) his Department's agencies.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","170923"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968377","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-09-13","<p>Other than my noble Friend, Lord Bourne, the Minister for Faith and Parliamentary Under Secretary of State for Wales, there are no other members of the House of Lords in the employ of the Department or our agencies.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-09-13T14:21:19.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968377/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968377/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968377/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-09-05","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Peers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, how many members of the House of Lords hold (a) paid and (b) unpaid roles within (i) his Department and (ii) his Department's agencies.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","170924"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968378","Department for International Trade","false","2018-09-13","<p>The Department for International Trade has one member of the Ministerial Team who is a member of the House of Lords who is unpaid.</p><p>There are also 10 PM Trade Envoys who are members of the House of Lords, this is an unpaid, voluntary role.</p><p> </p>","Meon Valley","George Hollingbery",,"2018-09-13T10:23:44.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968378/answer","Biography information for Sir George Hollingbery","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968378/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968378/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-09-05","Department for International Trade: Peers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many members of the House of Lords hold (a) paid and (b) unpaid roles within (i) his Department and (ii) his Department's agencies.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","170925"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968379","Department for Education","false","2018-09-14","<p>We do not hold this information for the Department for Education or its agencies. This is because we do not routinely capture it as part of the appointment process for paid and unpaid roles within the department or its agencies.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-09-14T13:24:46.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968379/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968379/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968379/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-09-05","Department for Education: Peers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many members of the House of Lords hold (a) paid and (b) unpaid roles within (i) his Department and (ii) his Department's agencies.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","170926"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968380","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-09-24","<p>The Department does not hold a definitive central record of all those who hold roles, either paid or unpaid, who are members of the House of Lords.</p><p> </p><p>One of the Department’s Ministers is a member of the House of Lords - Lord Gardiner of Kimble; Parliamentary Under Secretary of State for Rural Affairs and Biosecurity.</p><p> </p><p>There are 2 members of the House of Lords who are appointed as non-executive Board members across Defra’s Executive Agencies, non-Ministerial Departments and executive Non Departmental Public Bodies.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-09-24T08:13:35.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968380/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968380/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968380/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-09-05","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Peers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many members of the House of Lords hold (a) paid and (b) unpaid roles within (i) his Department and (ii) his Department's agencies.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","170927"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968381","Home Office","false","2018-09-13","<p>We are clear that social media companies must go further and faster in reducing the risks their platforms pose and are considering all options to make this happen.</p><p>This includes any changes to the law where necessary. It is unacceptable and irresponsible for companies to allow criminals to abuse their sites and companies need to take a proactive approach when tackling this material, including reporting illegal activity to the police.</p><p>The National Crime Agency and police employ a number of tactics to keep drugs off the street. Officials continue to work with internet providers to shut down UK-based websites found to be committing offences, building on work already underway to tackle the sale and supply of illegal drugs in the UK and overseas and tackle associated organised crime.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-09-13T17:00:55.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968381/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968381/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968381/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-09-05","Drugs: Social Media","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans his Department has to prevent social media companies from enabling illicit drugs to be sold on their platforms.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","170928"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968382","Department for Transport","false","2018-09-13","<p>We do not hold a central record of all those who hold roles, either paid or unpaid, who are members of the House of Lords.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-09-13T16:12:33.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968382/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968382/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968382/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-09-05","Department for Transport: Peers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many members of the House of Lords hold (a) paid and (b) unpaid roles within (i) his Department and (ii) his Department's agencies.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","170929"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968384","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-09-14","<p>The Department for Work and Pensions has one member of the House of Lords, holding a paid role. There is one member of the House of Lords, Whips Office holding an unpaid role in the department. This information is in the public domain and available to view online.</p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2018-09-14T12:01:26.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968384/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968384/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968384/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-09-05","Department for Work and Pensions: Peers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many members of the House of Lords hold (a) paid and (b) unpaid roles within (i) her Department and (ii) her Department's agencies.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","170930"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968385","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-09-14","<p>The data requested is not collected centrally.</p><p> </p><p>National Health Service organisations are locally responsible for the condition of their roads and car parks, which will includes potholes and are expected to keep their estate in an appropriate condition.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-09-14T11:23:04.05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968385/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968385/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968385/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-09-05","NHS: Roads","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what estimate he has made of the cost to the public purse of damage caused by potholes on the NHS estate in which year for which information is available; and what recent assessment he has made of trends in that level of cost.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","170931"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968386","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-09-13","<p>We do not hold a central record of all those who hold roles, either paid or unpaid, who are members of the House of Lords.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-09-13T16:42:40.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968386/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968386/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968386/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-09-05","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Peers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many members of the House of Lords hold (a) paid and (b) unpaid roles within (i) his Department and (ii) his Department's agencies.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","170932"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968387","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-09-13","<p>The Government recognises that the safety of mother and baby is paramount. Maternity services are a vital part of that but it is not possible to plan the exact time and place of birth, meaning there are occasions when a unit cannot safely accept more women into their care. In such cases, the only safe alternative is to close the unit temporarily.</p><p> </p><p>It is important of course, that where a unit closes, there are systems and guidelines in place to ensure pregnant women have access to the next closest maternity unit, where they are often diverted during such scenarios, as well as access to the type of care they have chosen, including midwifery-led care. Temporary closures in National Health Service maternity units are subject to well rehearsed safety measures which we expect trusts to use in order to safely manage peaks in admissions.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-09-13T09:46:55.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968387/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968387/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968387/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-09-05","Maternity Services: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what emergency support is in place for pregnant women affected by temporary closures of NHS maternity units throughout England.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","170933"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968388","Department for International Development","false","2018-09-12","<p>Ministerial remuneration and pension details are published in the Remuneration and Staff Report section of DFID’s <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dfid-annual-report-and-accounts-2017-to-2018" target="_blank">Annual Report and Accounts</a>.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-09-12T16:37:47.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968388/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968388/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968388/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-09-05","Department for International Development: Peers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many members of the House of Lords hold (a) paid and (b) unpaid roles within (i) her Department and (ii) her Department's agencies.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","170934"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968389","Scotland Office","false","2018-09-13","<p>The Office of the Secretary of State for Scotland has one member of the House of Lords in a paid role. Two members of the House of Lords carry out occasional limited activities in support of the department on an unpaid basis.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-09-13T12:28:19.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968389/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968389/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968389/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-09-05","Scotland Office: Peers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how many members of the House of Lords hold (a) paid and (b) unpaid roles within (i) his Department and (ii) his Department's agencies.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","170935"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968390","Wales Office","false","2018-09-11","<p>The Department’s Ministerial team includes one member of the House of Lords, who holds an unpaid position. The Department has no agencies.</p>","Eastleigh","Mims Davies",,"2018-09-11T10:30:58.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968390/answer","Biography information for Mims Davies","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968390/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968390/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2018-09-05","Wales Office: Peers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how many members of the House of Lords hold (a) paid and (b) unpaid roles within (i) his Department and (ii) his Department's agencies.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","170936"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968391","Northern Ireland Office","false","2018-09-14","<p>Two members of the House of Lords hold paid roles in the Northern Ireland Office. Lord Duncan of Springbank has been Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State since October 2017. Jonathan Caine has been Special Adviser since May 2010 and was created Lord Caine in September 2016. We do not hold a central record of all those who hold roles, either paid or unpaid, within the Department's agencies who are members of the House of Lords.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2018-09-14T13:35:41.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968391/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968391/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968391/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2018-09-05","Northern Ireland Office: Peers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many members of the House of Lords hold (a) paid and (b) unpaid roles within (i) his Department and (ii) his Department's agencies.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","170937"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968392","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-09-10","<p>The number of contracts secured by the Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency (MHRA) with the European Medicines Agency (EMA) in each of past five years is shown in the following table:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial year</p></td><td><p>Number of contracts</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>35</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>27</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>35</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016/17</p></td><td><p>41</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017/18</p></td><td><p>11</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The information included in the table is based on the EMA Committee on Human Medicinal Products (CHMP) rapporteurships allocated to the MHRA for assessment of new marketing authorisation applications.</p><p>The proportion of the income of the MHRA that came from the EMA in each of the past five years is shown in the following table:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial year</p></td><td><p>Proportion of income</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>6%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>6%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>6%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016/17</p></td><td><p>9%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017/18</p></td><td><p>8%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The source of the information is the MHRA’s Annual Report and Accounts for each of the past five years.</p><p>The number of bids submitted by the MHRA to carry out authorisations processes for the EMA based on the number of bids for CHMP rapporteurship for new marketing authorisation applications and the number of rapporteurships awarded in the last three financial years is shown in the following table:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial year</p></td><td><p>Number of bids submitted</p></td><td><p>Number of rapporteurships awarded</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>86</p></td><td><p>35</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016/17</p></td><td><p>87</p></td><td><p>41</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017/18</p></td><td><p>66</p></td><td><p>11</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Metrics for bids submitted prior to this time have not been recorded.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","170939 ; 170940","2018-09-10T16:07:16.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968392/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968392/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968392/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-09-05","Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many contracts the Medicines and Healthcare Products Regulatory Agency has secured with the European Medicines Agency to carry out authorisation processes in each of the past five years.","false","Biography information for Matthew Pennycook","Greenwich and Woolwich","Matthew Pennycook","170938"
