"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968835","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-09-17","<p>The National Shipbuilding Strategy envisages that the Type 31e will undertake a broad range of roles currently delivered by the Type 23 general purpose frigate, of which HMS Argyll is currently the first to leave service in 2023. We want the first Type 31e to enter service in 2023, with all five ships delivered by 2028.</p><p>The exact dates for the delivery of the Type 31e frigates are yet to be determined so it is too early to release the numbers of ships in service at any one time.</p>",,"Earl Howe","HL10120","2018-09-17T14:09:22.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968835/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968835/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968835/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-09-05","Type 31 Frigates","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether it is planned for the first Type 31e to replace HMS Argyll when she leaves service; and how long she will have been in commission at that date.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL10119"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968836","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-09-17","<p>The National Shipbuilding Strategy envisages that the Type 31e will undertake a broad range of roles currently delivered by the Type 23 general purpose frigate, of which HMS Argyll is currently the first to leave service in 2023. We want the first Type 31e to enter service in 2023, with all five ships delivered by 2028.</p><p>The exact dates for the delivery of the Type 31e frigates are yet to be determined so it is too early to release the numbers of ships in service at any one time.</p>",,"Earl Howe","HL10119","2018-09-17T14:09:22.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968836/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968836/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/968836/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-09-05","Frigates","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many frigates will be operational in the Royal Navy in (1) 2024, (2) 2025, (3) 2026, and (4) 2027.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL10120"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/947577","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-09-04","<p>The Government Buying Standards for food and catering services (GBSF) are mandatory for central Government and the NHS, and encouraged in the wider public sector, including schools and other educational establishments. The standards require that all meat and other animal derived products served must have been produced in compliance with UK legal standards for animal welfare.</p><p> </p><p>The Government’s balanced scorecard methodology for assessing the value of contract bids, which compliments the GBSF, rewards suppliers who provide produce, products or services which exceed minimum requirements. It includes award criteria for businesses which supply meat raised using enhanced welfare methods. The balanced scorecard is also mandatory for use in central Government departments, and encouraged for use in the broader public sector. Defra is working closely with other Government departments, including the Department for Education, to encourage uptake of the balanced scorecard approach.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-09-04T11:20:37.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/947577/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/947577/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/947577/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-09-04","Educational Institutions: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps he is taking to encourage procurement at (a) schools, (b) colleges, (c) universities and (d) other educational establishments to be compliant with high animal welfare standards.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","168178"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964602","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-09-11","<p>The British Government condemns the atrocities in Rakhine and is committed to working with international partners to bring those responsible to justice. The UK convened a meeting of the UN Security Council on 28 August chaired by the Minister for the Commonwealth and the United Nations to ensure the Council remains focused on the Rohingya crisis, including the need for accountability. When the Security Council considers the final UN Fact-Finding Mission report, we will have the opportunity to discuss all options to ensure accountability. On 6 September 2018, the Pre-Trial Chamber of the International Criminal Court (ICC) ruled that courtholders jurisdiction over the deportation of the Rohingya population from Burma to Bangladesh. The UK fully supports the court in its efforts to bring the perpetrators of human rights violations to justice.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-09-11T16:43:10.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964602/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964602/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964602/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-09-04","Rohingya: Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment the Government has made of the avenues available to bring the perpetrators of crimes against the Rohingya under international law to justice.","false","Biography information for Nick Thomas-Symonds","Torfaen","Nick Thomas-Symonds","169556"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964604","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-09-11","<p>​The British Government continues to be deeply concerned by religious and racial discrimination against minorities in Burma. The Government has repeatedly raised concerns about the treatment of minorities in Burma in the Human Rights Council in September 2017 and March 2018. The Minister for the Commonwealth and the United Nations raised the UK's concerns about the persecution faced by minority groups in Burma in his speech to the Human Rights Council of 27 February 2018. Our Embassy continues to support projects in Burma addressing the drivers of prejudice and inter-communal violence.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-09-11T16:45:33.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964604/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964604/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964604/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-09-04","Burma: Discrimination","1","House of Commons","To ask Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps the Government is taking to help tackle religious and racial discrimination in Burma.","false","Biography information for Nick Thomas-Symonds","Torfaen","Nick Thomas-Symonds","169558"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967117","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-09-04","<p>A new International Ocean Strategy was announced in June this year. When published it will underpin the UK’s leading role on marine protection. It will also provide this Government with a blueprint for international action that will support the long-term prosperity of the UK and our long-term commitment to protect the health of the marine environment.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","906728","2018-09-04T15:42:54.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967117/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967117/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967117/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-09-04","Nature Conservation: Seas and Oceans","1","House of Commons","What his policy is on global ocean conservation.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Pow","Taunton Deane","Rebecca Pow","906723"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967118","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-09-04","<p>The Prime Minister confirmed the UK’s full support to the peace process during her phone call with the new Colombian President on 9 August. The Foreign Secretary and Foreign Minister Holmes also discussed UN Security Council support to peace in Colombia when they met in New York on 24 August.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-09-04T15:46:00.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967118/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967118/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967118/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-09-04","Colombia: Peace Negotiations","1","House of Commons","What recent discussions he has had with his Colombian counterpart on the peace process in that country.","false","Biography information for Clive Efford","Eltham","Clive Efford","906724"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967119","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-09-04","<p>A new International Ocean Strategy was announced in June this year. When published it will underpin the UK’s leading role on marine protection. It will also provide this Government with a blueprint for international action that will support the long-term prosperity of the UK and our long-term commitment to protect the health of the marine environment.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","906723","2018-09-04T15:42:54.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967119/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967119/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967119/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-09-04","Nature Conservation: Seas and Oceans","1","House of Commons","What his policy is on global ocean conservation.","false","Biography information for Scott Mann","North Cornwall","Scott Mann","906728"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967120","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-09-04","<p>We need a negotiated political settlement to end the Syrian conflict. The UK is pragmatic about the nature of that settlement. We continue to work closely with the UN, international partners and Syrian opposition in support of the UN-led Geneva process to achieve it.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","906732","2018-09-04T15:45:13.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967120/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967120/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967120/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-09-04","Syria: Conflict Resolution","1","House of Commons","What political and diplomatic steps he is taking to help resolve the conflict in Syria.","false","Biography information for Ruth Cadbury","Brentford and Isleworth","Ruth Cadbury","906731"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967121","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-09-04","<p>We need a negotiated political settlement to end the Syrian conflict. The UK is pragmatic about the nature of that settlement. We continue to work closely with the UN, international partners and Syrian opposition in support of the UN-led Geneva process to achieve it.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","906731","2018-09-04T15:45:13.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967121/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967121/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967121/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-09-04","Syria: Conflict Resolution","1","House of Commons","What political and diplomatic steps he is taking to help resolve the conflict in Syria.","false","Biography information for Jeff Smith","Manchester, Withington","Jeff Smith","906732"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967400","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-09-17","<p>​The UK strongly supports the development of the Gazan gas fields. Over recent years, we have had extensive discussions with the Palestinian authorities on the development of the gas fields for the benefit of the Palestinian economy. The UK is not backing Israeli control of the gas fields. We have, however, been in discussions with the Israeli authorities to encourage them to enable the exploitation of these fields.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2018-09-17T14:37:14.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967400/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967400/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967400/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-09-04","Israel: Gaza","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what representations they have made to the government of Israel regarding its access to, and development of, Gaza’s oil and gas reserves.","false","Biography information for Lord Ahmed",,"Lord Ahmed","HL9902"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967401","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-09-18","<p>We do not reveal details of all the cases we have raised with the Turkish authorities nor the frequency with which we have raised them. However we will continue to raise key human rights issues, including individual cases where appropriate and in accordance with the criteria outlined in HL9904 with Turkey.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2018-09-18T15:12:18.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967401/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967401/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967401/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-09-04","Turkey: Detainees","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, further to the Written Answer from Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon on 26 July (HL9469), how many separate cases of detention in Turkey have been raised with the government of Turkey; and on how many occasions each of those cases of detention have been raised.","false","Biography information for Lord Balfe",,"Lord Balfe","HL9903"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967402","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-09-18","<p>As explained in HL9056, when deciding which specific detention cases to raise with the Turkish authorities we examine each on a case by case basis, noting the nature of the charge and length of detention. This year we have raised several cases, mainly concerning human rights defenders and journalists. We will continue to engage with the Turkish authorities on these important human rights concerns.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2018-09-18T15:11:48.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967402/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967402/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967402/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-09-04","Turkey: Detainees","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what criteria they use when deciding which cases of persons in detention to raise with the government of Turkey.","false","Biography information for Lord Balfe",,"Lord Balfe","HL9904"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967403","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-09-18","<p>We closely coordinate our approach to human rights-related work in Turkey with EU and other likeminded countries, such as Canada and Switzerland. We do not reveal details of all the cases we have collectively raised. We will continue to cooperate with our partners in this important field.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2018-09-18T15:08:34.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967403/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967403/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967403/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-09-04","Turkey: Detainees","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many cases of persons held in detention in Turkey have been raised with the government of Turkey as a result of discussions and decisions taken by the EU member states acting in political co-operation.","false","Biography information for Lord Balfe",,"Lord Balfe","HL9905"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967405","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-09-18","<p>There is no current refurbishment of the UK Permanent Representative to the European Union’s Residence in Brussels. We are, however, currently undertaking routine maintenance to the front of the building.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2018-09-18T15:30:09.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967405/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967405/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967405/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-09-04","UK Permanent Representation to the EU: Official Residences","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what are the cost, extent and purpose of the current refurbishment of the residence of the UK's Permanent Representative to the EU.","false","Biography information for Lord Balfe",,"Lord Balfe","HL9906"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967406","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-09-17","<p>Public Health England (PHE) has created a task and finish group made up of representatives from organisations across the sector including the Department, NHS England, the Local Government Association, the Association of Directors of Public Health, the Faculty of Sexual and Reproductive Health, the Royal College of General Practitioners, the Royal College of Nursing, the Royal College of Midwives, the Royal College of Gynaecology, Brook, and the Family Planning Association. The task and finish group will work together to inform the development and implementation of the reproductive health action plan. Alongside this, PHE is also working with a user reference group, made up of women who have experienced severe reproductive health issues in order to ensure the action plan reflects service users’ needs. The action plan is due to be published in March 2019.</p><p>In addition, PHE’s regional centres are developing an approach for localising the national research conducted and developing locally appropriate actions in addition to those being driven nationally. PHE are consulting with commissioners and providers in developing the action plan through workshops and presentations across the country and to ensure implementation of the action plan from 2019 onwards.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy","HL9908 ; HL9909","2018-09-17T14:03:21.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967406/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967406/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967406/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-09-04","Public Health","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what has been the process for developing Public Health England’s upcoming reproductive health action plan referenced on page 5 of Public Health England’s A consensus statement: reproductive health is a public issue; and when will that action plan be published.","false","Biography information for Baroness Barker",,"Baroness Barker","HL9907"
