"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967563","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-09-17","<p>I refer the noble Lord to the reply given by my hon. Friend, the previous Minister for Defence Procurement (Guto Bebb), in the House of Commons on 23 April 2018 to the hon. Member for Sheffield Central (Paul Blomfield) in response to Question number 904864.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2018-09-17T15:36:57.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967563/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967563/answer","20180423_904864_Type_26_Frigates.docx","20180423_904864_Type_26_Frigates.docx","904864 - Type 26 Frigates","904864 - Type 26 Frigates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967563/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-09-04","Type 26 Frigates","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government on what date the first Type 26 frigate will be in service with the Royal Navy.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL10044"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967564","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-09-14","<p>There are currently 21 designated days for flying the Union Flag on Government Buildings. These days have been set to mark special occasions by command of Her Majesty the Queen and on the advice of Government. As you suggest, any changes or additions are discussed with the Lord Chamberlain's Office.</p><p> </p><p>All other flag flying is deregulated and any organisation may fly any flag at any time, so long as they have the necessary planning permission. Therefore, organisations and individuals may fly the Red Ensign on Merchant Navy day if they wish.</p>",,"Lord Ashton of Hyde",,"2018-09-14T11:30:59.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967564/answer","Biography information for Lord Ashton of Hyde","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967564/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967564/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-09-04","Merchant Navy Day: Flags","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, further to the Written Answer by Baroness Neville-Rolfe on 26 April 2016 (HL7727), whether there have been any further discussions with the Lord Chamberlain’s office regarding the addition of flying the Red Ensign on Merchant Navy Day to the list of officially recognised flag days.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL10045"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967734","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-09-10","<p>Anyone who believes an offence is taking place, or has taken place, during a hunt (including any damage on public land) should report the matter to the police as they deal with complaints of illegal hunting. Decisions on the arrest and prosecution of those taking part in illegal hunting activities are matters for the police and prosecuting authorities.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","170399","2018-09-10T11:25:39.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967734/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967734/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967734/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-09-04","Hunting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps are taken to ensure that damage is not done to public land as a result of hunts.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","170398"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967735","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-09-10","<p>Anyone who believes an offence is taking place, or has taken place, during a hunt (including any damage on public land) should report the matter to the police as they deal with complaints of illegal hunting. Decisions on the arrest and prosecution of those taking part in illegal hunting activities are matters for the police and prosecuting authorities.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","170398","2018-09-10T11:25:39.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967735/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967735/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967735/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-09-04","Hunting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps are taken to ensure that the provisions of the Hunting Act 2004 are not violated on public land.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","170399"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967736","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-09-10","<p>No assessment has been made of the equity of legislation relating to dogs and dogs on hunts on public land.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-09-10T11:27:38.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967736/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967736/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967736/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-09-04","Hunting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what comparative assessment he has made of the equity of legislation relating to (a) dogs and (b) dogs on hunts on public land.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","170400"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967737","Home Office","false","2018-09-12","<p>The police and local authorities are empowered under Part IX of the Highways Act 1980 to take enforcement action against those who obstruct the public highway. How they do so is an operational matter in accordance with local plans and priorities.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-09-12T15:46:58.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967737/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967737/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967737/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-09-04","Hunting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps he is taking to enforce legislation relating to the blocking of public highways by hunt followers during a hunt; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","170401"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967738","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-09-12","<p>No.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-09-12T09:54:55.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967738/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967738/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967738/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-09-04","Hunting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to make illegal the production and sale of fox urine for the purpose of hunting.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","170402"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967739","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-09-10","<p>Defence provided approximately 100 soldiers from 4th Battalion, Royal Regiment of Scotland, to support the Greater Manchester Fire &amp; Rescue Service operation responding to the Saddleworth Moor fires between June and July 2018. The Defence Fire Risk Management Organisation (DFRMO) oversaw the training and equipment requirements for the Defence personnel involved.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-09-10T15:32:17.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967739/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967739/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967739/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-09-04","Fires: Moorland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what role the Ministry of Defence Fire Services undertook during firefighting operations near Saddleworth Moor between June 2018 and July 2018; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","170379"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967740","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-09-12","<p>The Department’s National Institute for Health Research (NIHR) recognises that chronic fatigue syndrome (CFS), also known as myalgic encephalomyelitis (ME), is a debilitating condition and is speaking with the UK CFS/ME Research Collaborative and patient representatives about how best to support a joined up approach to high quality research into this complex disorder.</p><p> </p><p>The NIHR welcomes funding applications for research into any aspect of human health, including CFS/ME; it is not usual practice to ring-fence funds for particular topics or conditions. Applications are subject to peer review and judged in open competition, with awards being made on the basis of the importance of the topic to patients and health and care services, value for money and scientific quality.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-09-12T11:49:21.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967740/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967740/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967740/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-09-04","Chronic Fatigue Syndrome","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, pursuant to the Answer of 4 June 2018 to Question 147821, on Chronic Fatigue Syndrome, what plans he has and what recent steps he has taken to expand this funding in the future.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","170278"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967741","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-09-10","<p>During the prolonged period of hot weather in summer 2018, two Supplementary Badger Control licenses were in operation, in West Somerset and West Gloucestershire.</p><p> </p><p>Natural England (NE) was in contact with the two Supplementary Badger Control companies on a regular basis during the period of prolonged hot weather.</p><p> </p><p>To assess the situation on the ground, NE staff have made three field visits to West Somerset and three field visits to West Gloucestershire. The visits found that best practise was being followed to avoid and mitigate against animals being exposed to extreme weather.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-09-10T12:21:15.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967741/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967741/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967741/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-09-04","Bovine Tuberculosis: Disease Control","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many times a monitor from Natural England visits a proposed culling site to assess whether the weather conditions are suitable for the badger cull in an area to proceed.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","170251"
